	<title>Democrats Hide Early Christmas Present For Cannabis Businesses In Covid 19 Relief Bill</title>
	<meta name="description" content="Therefore, almost no state-licensed cannabis businesses can legally obtain a bank account, process credit cards, or provide loans to small businesses and entrepreneurs. According to NORML, the main provisions of the proposed law – which would help marijuana businesses gain access to banking services – were included in the Democrats’ bill. The SAFE Banking Act explicitly allows banks and other financial institutions to work directly with state-legal marijuana businesses. For these reasons, NORML has long advocated that federal lawmakers enact The SAFE Banking Act. If passed by the House, this will mark the third time that the full body has approved SAFE Banking legislation." />
